Finally understood cleanup functions in useEffect! Claude explained with practical examples:

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(() => {...}, 1000);

  return () => clearInterval(timer); // Cleanup!
}, []);
```

**When cleanup runs:**
- Before component unmounts
- Before effect runs again (on dependency change)

Prevents memory leaks in subscriptions, timers, and event listeners.
